iration for and fulfillment of religious freedom. With America’s demographics rapidly changing from a majority white Protestant nation to a multiracial, multi-religious society, this book is an essential read for understanding how our past continues to shape our present—to the detriment of our nation’s future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aIslamophobiazUnited States. 0aMuslimszUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 0aReligion and politicszUnited States. 7aLAW / Civil Rights.2bisacsh1 aEsposito, John L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2021 Englishz978311075409408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2021z9783110753868oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069041508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052038230540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520382305423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520382305/original  a978-3-11-069041-5  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-073915-2  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075409-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Law 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGCb2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021